The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       
	Chennai: Indian skipper Mahendra Singh Dhoni Thursday decided to donate remuneration from two matches to the victims of the terror attacks in Mumbai. Dhoni had decided to donate the sum of two match fees to charity for victims of the Mumbai terror attacks, sources close to him revealed. But we dont know it would be from which two matches, they added.        
	Colombo: Sanath Jayasuriya has been recalled to Sri Lankas one-day squad for a tri-series with Bangladesh and Zimbabwe in January. Jayasuriya, 39, was rested for the recent five-match ODI series in Zimbabwe but will return for the limited-over leg of Sri Lankas Bangladesh tour. Mahela Udawatte, 22, has been dropped.        
	London: Shane Warne is the subject of a musical to be staged in Melbourne this week. Shane Warne: The Musical took three years in making. The show will open at the Athenaeum Theatre and is the brainchild of Eddie Perfect, an award-winning Australian singer and comedian.        
	Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) Thursday confirmed details of the process for the selection of venues for the ICC World Twenty20 2010 in the West Indies.        
	Islamabad: Pakistani umpire Asad Rauf said on Thursday that he has no security reservations about officiating at Test matches in India later this month.          
	New Delhi: Ranjeet Virali Murugesan reached the semi-finals of the national mens tennis championship with a straight-sets victory over Arjun Gautham even as second seed Rohan Gide was shown the door by unseeded Sriram Balaji Narayanswamy here Thursday.                                                                                                                                                                                 
